Globaltrans Gains Most in Month on Bets Share Slump Overdone

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-08-12T10:24:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-12/globaltrans-gains-most-in-month-on-bets-share-slump-overdone.html
Globaltrans Investment Plc (GLTR) , Russia’s
biggest non-state rail operator, rallied the most in more than a
month in  London  on bets its declines are overdone.  The shares gained as much as 7.7 percent, their biggest
intraday advance since June 29, and traded 3.3 percent higher at
$14.15 as of 2:13 p.m. in Moscow, paring the stock’s drop this
week to 16 percent.  GlobalTrans shares are “close to the floor,” Andrew Howell and Maria Gratsova, analysts at Citigroup Inc., said in
an e-mailed report today in which they recommending buying the
stock.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  